Iâ€™ve had [disquiet.com](https://disquiet.com) flowing into my RSS reader for several years at this point, but it was only this week that I realised what Mark Weidenbaum is doing with [his weekend post:](https://disquiet.com/2022/04/23/twitter-com-disquiet-noyes-mingus-bpm/) collating a selection of his activity from Twitter that week, and presenting it as a blogpost, with added context and annotation. At the time of writing, this site is pretty much my only outlet on the web, but if I ever take up posting on other platforms, that summary post may be something that I try a version of. It feels adjascent to the [POSSE](https://indieweb.org/POSSE) approach to online publishing, with which I feel aligned. In Weidenbaum's implementation, he's using siloed platforms, but doing the work of ensuring that a curated version of the same material appears on his own site.[^1]  
